post_text:
Chromebook pick-up for all virtual select students is happening today! This event will take place in the driveline and parking lot area. You will not need to get out of your car. Each vehicle will pull around to the back of the building in order to receive their chromebook(s). Once you have received the chromebook(s) checked out to your scholar(s), we will have you pull forward to a parking lot space to make sure that each chromebook will successfully login. Once your Chromebook is logged in, a staff member will check in with you and you will be free to go!

Virtual Select - Thursday, September 10th
10:00 am-11:00 am: Last Name A-K
11:00 am-12:00 pm: Last Name L-Z
5:00 pm-6:00 pm: Last Name A-K
6:00 pm-7:00 pm: Last Name L-Z

These pick-up times will allow us to ensure social distancing and a smaller size group for safety. Please stick with the time that your group has been assigned to ensure you are doing your part to assist us with this! Please limit the amount of people that you bring to pick-up. Only 1 parent/guardian and the registered scholars are asked to come.üíª üíª üíª

We miss you and are so excited to welcome you back to school this fall! We are planning for a school year of learning together in an in-person classroom environment. However, we realize things can change between now and the first day of school. Take a moment to watch this video to hear more about how we‚Äôre preparing for the 2020-21 school year. We created detailed plans around four learning scenarios. These plans are in-line with our state's department of education plan, which outlines required and recommended safety protocols for the 2020-21 school year based on the status of coronavirus in our community.
For the most up to date information on back to school plan, please visit: https://www.nhaschools.com/en/COVID-19

post_text:
Spirit Week Activity
Hello TEA!
This week we are going to do it a little different for our Spirit Day activities. We are going to have a scavenger hunt that will last the whole week. You can spread out the things to find over different days of the week or do it all in one day. So, the objective is to find objects in your house that start with the same letter as each of the letters in the following saying. "WE ARE TAYLOR EXEMPLAR ACADEMY" Now you cannot use the same object twice, and try to be as creative as you can. We will post this on our Facebook site and please feel free to post a list of things you found or take a picture of all of your objects. Have fun TEA and show us your SPIRIT!

post_text:
WEEKLY CHALLENGE #2 - FUN CHALLENGE - SPEED DRESSING!

This weekly challenge will run from Friday, March 27th thru Wednesday, April 1st at 8pm.

Challenge: Fastest time to put 5 outfits on over a set of pajamas and do a celebration dance!

How to do it: Starting with wearing a pair of pajamas, have 5 additional outfits laid out. The outfits must include: shirt, pants, socks. Have a parent or older sibling help you videotape your speed dressing challenge. The time stops after you have all of the clothing on and you have completed your celebration dance!

How to share results: Upload the video as a comment to this Facebook Post In the comment section of your video, please write the total time it took and your child's name.

PLEASE MAKE SURE THAT YOUR CHILD IS IN A FULL SET OF PAJAMAS BEFORE STARTING!

Winners will be announced via newsletter next week and on Facebook!

Edit - pictures not able to be loaded-send a Facebook messenger after commenting that you completed it!

Good morning TEA families! We are excited to present our first school-wide challenge!
The Challenge: Use a Recipe and Cook or Bake with a Family Member
What you Need to Do: Choose a recipe to make. Use math and double or half the recipe - take a picture of your math. Make the recipe with at least one family member and take pictures along the way.
By Wednesday, March 25th at 8pm comment on this post with your recipe and pictures of your math and your time creating the recipe with your family!
Bonus points will be given for TEA Pride being shown in the cooking or pictures!
We will be choosing winners based on meeting the expectations and how much fun it looks like you had from the pictures!
Winners will be announced on Friday, March 27th!

The other spirit wear items can be worn during jean days or dress down days.

Thank you!
